 PITTSBURGH REGIONAL LIBRARY CENTER: A CASE STUDY ON THE DEVELOPMENT OF A'FULL SERVICE NETWORK'.EXAMINES THE DEVELOPMENT, OPERATION AND FUTURE OF THE PITTSBURGH REGIONALLIBRARY CENTER (PRLC) A MULTI-STATE, MULTI-TYPE LIBRARY NETWORK. INCORPORATEDIN 1967, PRLC HAS DEVELOPED INTO A 'FULL SERVICE NETWORK' WHICH PROVIDES OCLCSERVICE, RLG/RLIN SERVICE, CONTINUING EDUCATION, ON-LINE UNION LISTING,CONSULTING, COOPERATIVE PURCHASING AND RECIPROCAL BORROWING TO ITS 65 LIBRARYMEMBERS IN 3 STATES. DISCUSSES PRLC'S PLANS FOR THE 1980S